brainly_data.question: A wave with a wavelength of three meters forms in water with a depth of one meter. what type of wave is it?
brainly_data.subject: Chemistry

all_answers.question: A wave with a wavelength of three meters forms in water with a depth of one meter. what type of wave is it?
all_answers.subject: Chemistry
all_answers.text: A wave of the above dimensions would be considered a long shore wave.
